3 DATA
4 TEXT Samuel Judah:
5 CONT
5 CONT New York patriot, son of Baruch Judah, was born in New York Aug. 19, 
5 CONC 1728; married, Kislew 29, 1759, Jessie, daughter of Alexander Jonas, 
5 CONC of London (died in New York, May 29, 1818, aged 82 years). He was one 
5 CONC of the signers of the decision to enforce the non-importation 
5 CONC agreement against England in 1770; he died in Philadelphia Oct. 19, 
5 CONC 1781, aged 53, the father of twelve children (Wolf, l.c. p. 34; 
5 CONC "Publ." iv. 89; v. 205; vi. 102, 108); Samuel Judah, of Montreal, 
5 CONC Canada; sympathizer with the American cause in the Revolutionary war 
5 CONC ("Publ." iv. 224); Samuel Judah, served in Company K, 20th Indiana 
5 CONC Infantry, during the Civil war (Wolf, l.c. p. 178).
5 CONT
5 CONT Read more: 
5 CONC http://www.jewishencyclopedia.com/view.jsp?artid=599&letter=J#ixzz0jOu
5 CONC ZZhWH
