1 CONT Source Description
1 CONT
1 CONT This database is an index to individuals enumerated in the 1900 United 
1 CONC States Federal Census, the Twelfth Census of the United States. Census 
1 CONC takers recorded many details including each person's name, address, 
1 CONC relationship to the head of household, color or race, sex, month and 
1 CONC year of birth, age at last birthday, marital status, number of years 
1 CONC married, the total number of children born of the mother, the number 
1 CONC of those children living, birthplace, birthplace of father and mother, 
1 CONC if the individual was foreign born, the year of immigration and the 
1 CONC number of years in the United States, the citizenship status of 
1 CONC foreign-born individuals over age twenty-one, occupation, and more. 
1 CONC Additionally, the names of those listed on the population schedule are 
1 CONC linked to actual images of the 1900 Federal Census. Learn more...
